@node intro "Introduction"
Window Walker is a program for all of you who love having small men walking
on your Workbench. There are some old programs with this theme around, but
this one stands out in the meaning that it works (theoretically) on any
screen resolution you're throwing at it. Different screen depths shouldn't
be a problem either. Note though that some weird flickering and speed loss
could appear on some systems. Please leave a bug report if you experience
this. CyberGFX SHOULD be treated more nicely now, but a report on that
would be nice.

If you don't want to control the little man, known among my friends as the
"sluring" by the way, there is a mode available where he walks on his own
and tries to jump to another window if he reaches an edge.
@endnode

