@node usage "Usage"
Window Walker can be started from WB or CLI.

CLI arguments: AUTO/S,NOWINDOW/S

AUTO:     Start the program in autowalking mode.
NOWINDOW: Don't open the control window.

These options can also be given as tooltypes from WB.

To control the man you need the window opened by the program. Have that
window active and use the cursor keys as follows:

      LEFT - go left
     RIGHT - go right
        UP - jump
 LEFT+JUMP - jump left
RIGHT+JUMP - jump right
     SPACE - toggle autowalk

The program terminates if the window is closed or the man falls down.
@endnode

